 a copycat having no gooseberries eats a candy gooseberry made of \nsugar syrup and green color. The copycat is obviously not going to get \nany health benefit from that candy gooseberry. If that person gets too \ntechnical and asks about how much the gooseberry should weigh, what \nshould be the radius, how exactly it should be eaten etc, I may say that \nit does not matter and just eat it however you want and wait for the day \nyou get access to a real raw gooseberry. That does not amount to calling \nthe original gooseberry eater foolish!\n\n&quot;Scientific&quot; is a word that is understood in a very narrow sense today. \nScience as we understand now-a-days is limited to the material world and \nobjects in it. But, spiritual sadhana, on the other hand, is not limited \nto the material world. So the science that governs spiritual sadhana is \nnot limited to the material world.\n\nJust as one not having access to a telescope cannot do visual \nexperiments related to observing and measuring planets and stars, \nsimilarly one unable to perceive one&#39;s own subtle body cannot do real \nanganyas (i.e. place syllables in various places in it). Of course, just \nto get practice or just for fun, one can pretend to look through a toy \ntelescope and pretend that one is seeing so and so star or planet. \nSimilarly, one can touch the tips of the corresponding fingers and say \nthe syllable and pretend that the syllable has been placed there.\n\nIf one follows yama and niyama, if one removes all conditioning using \nwhatever sadhana one follows, if one achieves an equanimous mind that is \nestablished in Truth, then one&#39;s mind itself is a powerful instrument \nthat can helps one master spiritual science. On the other hand, if one&#39;s \nmind is colored by dense conditioning and is vibrating to the tune of \napparent material reality, then one is lacking the scientific instrument \nfor making accurate observations and measurements in the spiritual \nrealm.\n\nBest regards,\nNarasimha\n-------------------------------------------------------------------\n   Free Jyotish Software, Free Jyotish Lessons, Jyotish Writings,\n&quot;Do It Yourself&quot; ritual manuals for short Homam and Pitri Tarpana:\n                   http://www.VedicAstrologer.org\n      Films that make a difference: http://SaraswatiFilms.org\n      Spirituality: http://groups.yahoo.com/group/vedic-wisdom\n   Jyotish writings: http://groups.yahoo.com/group/JyotishWritings\n-------------------------------------------------------------------\n\nOn Sun, Jan 30, 2011 at 11:53 PM, Se Am wrote:\n\n    Our ancestors did not do anything foolishly\nthey had a scientific approach,\nonly the scientific approach has disappeared\nso I do not agree with you\nif you can define homa scientifically then you have to define anganyas\n\n\n___________________________________\n\nFrom: Narasimha PVR Rao &lt;pvr@...&gt;\nTo: vedic-wisdom@yahoogroups.com\nSent: Wed, January 26, 2011 4:13:01  AM\nSubject: [vedic-wisdom] Re: Angnyaas\n\n\n\nNamaste,\n\nAs I said before, the nyaasa people do today is merely a formality. \nNyasa literally means placement. You *place* certain sound combinations \nin certain chakras (energy centers) in various body parts (e.g. tips of \nring fingers, tips of little fingers, heart, top of head, between eyes \netc).\n\nIf you touch a body part in a particular way and say the sound, will \nthat really *place* that sound in that chakra? Will that chakra vibrate \nwith that sound then? Of course, not.\n\nThose who have been taught a procedure by somebody can follow what they \nare taught. Those who do not know need not worry.\n\nJust as the streets and surroundings of your house may automatically be \nrepaired if the Prime Minister of India decides to visit your house, \nvarious chakras in your subtle body will automatically vibrate with the \ncorrect sounds if the deity decides to express to you in some form or \nthe other.\n\nBuilding devotion and surrender is far m