adha etc- used at different \n&gt;&gt; times. Do not look for meaning in these individual words or phrases.\n&gt;&gt;\n&gt;&gt; I have explained what the intention is.  None of this is asking for \n&gt;&gt; power. Indeed there is no power in the universe which is outside \n&gt;&gt; oneself- again this is a simplification.\n&gt;&gt; Dont get lost in the forest of intellectual understanding. \n&gt;&gt; Practice.....intellectual understanding by itself is useless( just as \n&gt;&gt; knowing how an internal combustion engine works does not make one the \n&gt;&gt; owner of a car).\n&gt;&gt; These words may not be packaged as well as they can be- its a bit \n&gt;&gt; late and the flowery speech part has gone to sleep :-)\n&gt;&gt; --- In vedic-wisdom@yahoogroups.com, Se Am &lt;mahalaxmyey@&gt; wrote:\n&gt;&gt;&gt;\n&gt;&gt;&gt; so  Netratrayaay Voushat. means give power to eyes\n&gt;&gt;&gt; what is  meaning of both words Shikhaayei Vashat. combined\n&gt;&gt;&gt;\n&gt;&gt;&gt; ________________________________ From: S &lt;tejomaya101@&gt; To: \n&gt;&gt;&gt; vedic-wisdom@yahoogroups.com Sent: Sat, January 15, 2011 3:59:58 PM \n&gt;&gt;&gt; Subject: [vedic-wisdom] Re: Angnyaas\n&gt;&gt;&gt;\n&gt;&gt;&gt; Shikha is the know one ties in the hair at the back. You can also \n&gt;&gt;&gt; use a rubber\n&gt;&gt;\n&gt;&gt;&gt; band or ribbon or the like. Even if you are a male, it is good to \n&gt;&gt;&gt; tie ones hair\n&gt;&gt;&gt; before any act of worship if you have enough hair to do so. This \n&gt;&gt;&gt; should be done\n&gt;&gt;&gt;  at the top,back of ones head.\n&gt;&gt;&gt; Netra is eyes.\n&gt;&gt;&gt; S\n&gt;&gt;&gt; --- In vedic-wisdom@yahoogroups.com, Se Am &lt;mahalaxmyey@&gt; wrote:\n&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;\n&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt; thank you for the information i know sirase means head,hridyay \n&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt; means heart ,kavachay means shield, but what is Shikhaayei and \n&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt; Netratrayaay thanks Se Am\n&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;\n&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;\n&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;\n&gt;&gt